infinite combo limiters is dumb
Prossh Strikes again.

wow I'm grumpy this morning apparently
the problem isn't infinite combos that people need to realize
it's the fact that they lost that is making them feel bad
they feel like they lost because of something "easy"
so they blame it on the combo instead of the things they could have done to stop it before it happened
I mean, I could complain just as much about rhys and his ability to double is tokens
"you should only be able to double your tokens as often as you cast your commander"
it's dumb
How do you really feel Patrick?
I feel like I haven't had enough coffee yet
To counterpoint that though Patrick, your combos aren't necessarily the combos people get salty about
is it easy to win by combo? sometimes, but that can also be said for running out craterhoof
which does get some flack
but again, hoof isn't the problem, the problem was that no one board wiped the turn before
and fair enough, but I have to ask, how often do you see inifinite combos like that outside of cedh?
< this guy
and which ones are they?
Mirri has Devoted Druid + Ballista/Mana Sink
Omnath has Perilous Forays + Amulet of Vigor
Muldrotha has Aluren
Muldrotha is a combo machine actually
well that's true
she's silly
but that's like saying paradox engine is silly, of course it is
Presence of Gond + Intruder Alarm etc
but all these things have answers

but if you play against it enough to think "we should make a rule against it"
you're building your deck wrong

and again, that's not a rules issue

punch him in the dick for night

he wasn't a good friend if he can't take a dick punch
just saying
If it's going to lead to more fun for the group, what's the issue is my thing?
good friends take dick punches for each other
like I said, I'm being a little ornery for some reason

which is why I shouldn't be on twitter
